article.headline: Drexel 72, Sam Houston St. 61
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Drexel scored 13 points off 11 second-half turnovers by Sam Houston State to win 72-61 Thursday night in the quarterfinal round of the NIT Season Tip-Off. The Dragons (2-0), who won in front of a record crowd of 2,437, advance to play No. 1 ranked Duke in the semifinals Wednesday night at Madison Square Garden. Drexel opened the second half with a 13-0 run that broke a 33-33 tie at halftime and spanned 5:56. Bashir Mason capped off the run with a steal, a drive down the court and a layup to put the Dragons ahead 46-33. Mason was one of four Dragons to score in double-digits, leading the team with 18. Chris Jordan ended the run with a dunk to cut the lead to 11. The Dragons survived an 8-0 run by the Bearkats (1-1) late in the second half. Ryan Bright scored on a pair of free throws with 4:28 left in the game to whittle Drexel's lead to 62-57, but it was the closest Sam Houston State would get. Bright scored a game-high 21 points and had 12 rebounds. The Dragons sealed the win scoring 10 of the game's final 14 points. In the second half, Drexel shot 59 percent from the field making 16 of 27 field goal attempts. Drexel outscored Sam Houston State 30-11 in points off turnovers. Frank Elegar and Chaz Crawford each blocked three shots for the Dragons. Crawford, Mason and Dominick Mejia each added three steals for Drexel.
